                            <h2>Chicago Public Media</h2>
                            <h4 class="serif">• September 2013 • Monica Eng</h4>
                        </header>

                        <p>.....When Arun Sampathavivat opened his acclaimed restaurant in 1985, he came to the project with multiple academic degrees, but zero culinary training. No matter. Within a few years, the budding chef would transform a drab Northwest Side corner of Kedzie Avenue into a world class dining destination, earning the industry's highest accolades.... <a href="http://www.wbez.org/can-arun-sampanthavivat-create-chicago-neighborhood-scratch-108701">read more</a></p>


                        <header>
